.TH CLAUDE-MONITOR 1 "2026-05-21" "claude-monitor 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
claude-monitor \- Linux usage widget and CLI for Claude AI subscriptions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B claude-monitor
[\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B claude-monitor
tracks Claude AI subscription usage (session 5-hour and weekly 7-day quotas)
and displays the current utilization in your system tray. A CLI surface
mirrors every tray action so you can integrate with waybar, polybar, tmux,
shell prompts, and scripts.

Bare invocation launches the tray. Use subcommands for non-GUI access.

.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\fBtray\fR
Launch the system tray (default if no subcommand given).
.TP
\fBstatus\fR [\fB--account\fR \fINAME\fR] [\fB--json\fR | \fB--format\fR \fITPL\fR | \fB--quiet\fR]
Print current usage for one account.
.TP
\fBaccounts\fR [\fB--json\fR]
List all configured accounts.
.TP
\fBadd-token\fR [\fITOKEN\fR] [\fB--email\fR \fIEMAIL\fR]
Add a Claude account by OAuth access token. Reads from stdin if no argument.
.TP
\fBimport-env\fR \fIFILE\fR
Import ACCOUNT_EMAIL_N and ACCOUNT_KEY_N pairs from a .env file.
.TP
\fBremove\fR \fINAME\fR
Remove an account and its usage history.
.TP
\fBpoll\fR [\fB--account\fR \fINAME\fR]
Force a poll cycle. Delegates to the running tray via D-Bus when possible.
.TP
\fBpin\fR \fINAME\fR
Pin an account to drive the tray badge percentage.
.TP
\fBunpin\fR
Clear the tray pin (falls back to first-found account).
.TP
\fBprobe\fR [\fB--account\fR \fINAME\fR]
Reset the OAuth Usage endpoint state machine back to \(lqhealthy\(rq and
attempt one poll. Use after a long backoff.
.TP
\fBversion\fR
Print the binary version and exit.

.SH STATUS OUTPUT FORMATS
.TP
plain (default)
Human-readable single line.
.TP
\fB--json\fR
Machine-readable JSON object suitable for jq.
.TP
\fB--format\fR \fITEMPLATE\fR
Go text/template against the same fields as \fB--json\fR. Useful for
status-bar integrations.
Example: \fIclaude-monitor status --format='LLM {{.PrimaryPercent}}%%'\fR

.SH EXIT CODES (\fBstatus\fR)
.TP
0
Primary usage below 75%.
.TP
10
At or above 75% (caution).
.TP
20
At or above 90% (warning).
.TP
30
At or above 95% (critical).
.TP
1
Error: no data, network failure, etc.

.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.local/share/claude-monitor/usage.db\fR
SQLite database (WAL). Permissions enforced at 0600 / 0700.
.TP
\fI~/.config/claude-monitor/config.toml\fR
TOML configuration. Auto-created on first run.
.TP
\fI~/.local/state/claude-monitor/debug.log\fR
Rolling log file (slog JSON). Rotated at 5 MB.
.TP
\fI~/.config/autostart/claude-monitor.desktop\fR
Autostart entry; presence controlled by the Settings window or by the user.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Add an account from stdin
\fIecho "$TOKEN" | claude-monitor add-token\fR
.TP
Waybar custom module
\fI{"custom/claude": {"exec": "claude-monitor status --format='{{.PrimaryPercent}}%%'", "interval": 60}}\fR
.TP
tmux right-status
\fIset -g status-right '#(claude-monitor status --format=\(dq{{.PrimaryPercent}}%%\(dq)'\fR
.TP
Shell warning above 90%
\fIif ! claude-monitor status --quiet; then echo "Claude usage high!"; fi\fR

